arts.ttl: PLAYER RATINGS - How did Carlisle United fare against Colchester?
arts.sum: RATINGS: Carlisle United drew 0-0 with Colchester United – so how did we rate the players at Brunton Park?

arts.ttl: Carlisle United 0 Colchester United 0 - match report as U's claim away point
arts.sum: Colchester goalkeeper Matt Macey made two excellent stops in the second half while his Carlisle counterpart Gabe Breeze made a superb save to deny Lyle Taylor. Colchester did go close in the 12th minute when Taylor's effort was saved by goalkeeper Breeze from close range, after Jamie McDonnell's overhead kick flew into his path.

arts.ttl: Defender suffers injury blow in Carlisle United's draw with Colchester
arts.sum: Josh Williams is set to be ruled out for up to six weeks after suffering a hamstring injury in Carlisle United's 0-0 draw with Colchester.

arts.ttl: Mark Hughes’ first home game in charge of bottom side Carlisle ends in stalemate
arts.sum: The goalkeepers were on top throughout the game.

arts.ttl: Carlisle United draw with Colchester as both keepers star
arts.sum: REPORT: Carlisle United earned their first point under Mark Hughes as goalkeepers at both ends starred in a goalless draw with Colchester.

arts.ttl: Carlisle United v Colchester United - odds, predicted line-ups, team news
arts.sum: Colchester could welcome back winger JK Gordon for today's game at Carlisle. He is set to come up against Carlisle's young striker Joe Hugill, who is on loan from Manchester United and had previously been on loan at Wigan Athletic, in the first half of this season.

arts.ttl: Colchester boss Cowley on his trip to watch Carlisle United
arts.sum: Colchester United manager Danny Cowley insists Carlisle United have “a lot of quality” ahead of this weekend’s clash at Brunton Park.

arts.ttl: Young midfielder departs Colchester United to sign for League of Ireland side
arts.sum: He has now returned to Northern Ireland and boss Colchester boss Danny Cowley believes it will be a good move for the versatile youngster. Thompson joined Forest when he was 16 after impressing for Northern Irish side Crusaders and spent two years at the City Ground club.

arts.ttl: New Carlisle United signing Dennis's goal highlights
arts.sum: WATCH: See footage of new Blues frontman Matt Dennis in goalscoring form for his previous clubs.

arts.ttl: Carlisle United coach quits - as Blues appoint replacement
arts.sum: Carlisle United have moved quickly to replace goalkeeping coach Tom Weal who has left the club for a reported move to Sunderland.
